The paper deals with clustering of polygonal curves in Euclidean space, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which are topics in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the Fr\'echet distance, which is a similarity measure used in information retrieval and pattern recognition (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Gonzalez' algorithm, which is a well-known heuristic for clustering problems (cs.CC).
